ALWCOMBORDER - "Warning is reported" during verilator build for always_comb usage. In below scenario, the variable on the left hand side should be ignored (add to exception list) for this warning and should not be part of sensitive list even if it is used on the right hand side for the calculation, as this is getting assigned during this block execution.

Warning: %Warning-ALWCOMBORDER:  Always_comb variable driven after use: 'a'

Problem code:
```
module demo();

logic [3:0] a;
logic [3:0] b;
bit [3:0] r;
logic clk;
always @(posedge clk) 
begin
    r<=a;
    $display("Demo value A %p \n", a);
    $display("Demo value R %p \n", r);
end
always_comb begin
    $display("Combo value A %p \n", a);
    if (a<4) begin
        a = r + 1'b1;
        $display("Combo a< 4 value A %p \n", a);
    end
    else begin
        a = 1;
        $display("Combo else value A %p \n", a);
    end
end
initial begin
    clk = 0;
    repeat(10) begin 
        #1;
        clk = ~clk;
    end
end
endmodule.
```

